The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning algorithm that achieves state-of-the-art performance on continuous control benchmark tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on control tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) or systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions that it achieves performance improvements on benchmark tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as benchmark tasks are often used to evaluate computer vision algorithms.
